Package: crimsondown
Title: An updated R Markdown thesis template using the bookdown package
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chester", "Ismay", email = "chester.ismay@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Nick", "Solomon", email = "nick@nicksolomon.me", role = "aut"),
    person("Louisa H.", "Smith", email = "louisahsmith@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut")))
Description: Using the bookdown package and building off of an earlier implentation
    of Harvard GSAS dissertation formatting requirements in LaTeX, as well as the
    thesisdown package, this package aims to encourage reproducible research using
    simple Markdown syntax while embedding all of the R code to produce plots
    and analyses as well.
Maintainer: Louisa H. Smith <louisahsmith@gmail.com>
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.0),
    bookdown
Suggests:
    officedown,
    redoc
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: pandoc (>= 1.18) - http://pandoc.org
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
